race.comment: GINGERIFFIC (8) is clearly the one they have to beat. Raced at Geraldton third-up and impressed winning her Maiden finishing hard from a long way back. She's capable of using the inside barrier and this contest doesn't look much tougher. PLAYBALL (3) also peaks and improved beaten 3.2L at Ascot last time when he stalked the lead. Maps well and is better placed today. ZAC LUVS TO FLY (1) resumes and went okay early in his previous preparation. Might have to do it the hard way, but the 2kg claim assists and his best would have him in the money.  PLAYFUL STAR (10) has an inside gate and may be the best of the remainder.
